the moment they can.

508
00:28:52,071 --> 00:28:53,805
No, it's not about that.

509
00:28:53,839 --> 00:28:56,542
It's just, well,
I'm such a fool

510
00:28:56,576 --> 00:28:58,743
and I suppose I was
trying to be a gentleman,

511
00:28:58,778 --> 00:29:01,446
- but my friend here, she--
- Don't.

512
00:29:01,481 --> 00:29:03,915
We don't need to see a doctor.

513
00:29:03,949 --> 00:29:07,285
I'm sure it's something that would be
covered by your medical expertise.

514
00:29:07,319 --> 00:29:09,420
What are you talking about?

515
00:29:09,454 --> 00:29:11,222
She's a little embarrassed,

516
00:29:11,256 --> 00:29:13,491
but she drank furniture polish.

517
00:29:13,525 --> 00:29:15,293
Honey, why'd you do that?

518
00:29:15,327 --> 00:29:18,429
She wasn't wearing her glasses.

519
00:29:18,463 --> 00:29:21,198
You do need to see a doctor.
Why didn't you tell me that?

520
00:29:21,199 --> 00:29:22,799
I'm sorry. I really
never know what to do.

521
00:29:22,800 --> 00:29:24,267
I thought I'd just
leave it up to you.

522
00:29:24,302 --> 00:29:27,070
Okay, sweetheart.
Ramirez.

523
00:29:28,239 --> 00:29:30,106
Take her to bed four.

524
00:29:33,311 --> 00:29:35,111
She'll be fine.

525
00:29:54,563 --> 00:29:56,531
You look perfect.

526
00:29:56,565 --> 00:29:59,166
Well, I had three hours
to get ready.

527
00:29:59,201 --> 00:30:01,236
I don't know if the shoes go.

528
00:30:01,270 --> 00:30:02,803
They do.

529
00:30:06,908 --> 00:30:08,609
Where are we going?

530
00:30:09,944 --> 00:30:11,978
We're not going anywhere.

531
00:30:12,012 --> 00:30:13,747
Are you kidding me?

532
00:30:13,781 --> 00:30:16,450
Why would you think
you're going anywhere?

533
00:30:16,484 --> 00:30:18,785
You are for me.

534
00:30:18,819 --> 00:30:22,356
You exist in this room
for my pleasure.

535
00:30:24,558 --> 00:30:26,425
Are we going to eat?

536
00:30:26,460 --> 00:30:28,561
Don't ask any more questions.

537
00:30:28,595 --> 00:30:30,062
Take off your dress.

538
00:30:31,931 --> 00:30:34,833
Take off everything for me.

539
00:31:08,166 --> 00:31:10,133
Like that?

540
00:31:48,337 --> 00:31:50,304
I think you look
worse than I do.

541
00:31:52,574 --> 00:31:54,575
Well, I slept on
the floor of my office.

542
00:31:54,609 --> 00:31:56,276
They didn't give you a couch?

543
00:31:56,311 --> 00:31:59,213
I couldn't find it.
Draper knocked me out.

544
00:31:59,247 --> 00:32:01,314
Not literally.

545
00:32:01,349 --> 00:32:04,984
I'm sure there's
a lot of work to do.

546
00:32:05,018 --> 00:32:06,953
It's got nothing
to do with work.

547
00:32:06,987 --> 00:32:09,722
He seems more interested in me
than he is in the work.

548
00:32:09,756 --> 00:32:11,890
But you're not
very interesting.

549
00:32:11,924 --> 00:32:14,727
He doesn't know that.

550
00:32:15,795 --> 00:32:17,295
What's he like?

551
00:32:19,666 --> 00:32:22,033
He's mysterious.

552
00:32:22,068 --> 00:32:24,235
But I can't tell
if he's putting it on.

553
00:32:25,771 --> 00:32:27,605
He doesn't talk
for long stretches,

554
00:32:27,639 --> 00:32:30,307
and then he's
incredibly eloquent.

555
00:32:30,342 --> 00:32:32,910
He's very successful.

556
00:32:32,944 --> 00:32:35,680
You didn't think
he was charmless, did you?

557
00:32:35,714 --> 00:32:37,715
You learned to work with me.

558
00:32:37,750 --> 00:32:39,283
And look at you.

559
00:32:41,318 --> 00:32:43,420
If I wait patiently
by the river,

560
00:32:43,454 --> 00:32:45,922
the body of my enemy
will float by.

561
00:32:45,956 --> 00:32:49,125
Such a waste of energy.

562
00:32:49,159 --> 00:32:52,596
Give him the early rounds.
He'll tire himself out.

563
00:32:55,733 --> 00:32:58,334
Go home, shower,

564
00:32:58,369 --> 00:33:01,737
walk back in there
like you own half the place.

565
00:33:20,256 --> 00:33:22,257
I'll be back at dinnertime.

566
00:33:22,292 --> 00:33:23,825
Because you live here.

567
00:33:23,859 --> 00:33:25,294
No, I don't.

568
00:33:25,328 --> 00:33:26,895
There's a hamper
full of laundry

569
00:33:26,930 --> 00:33:28,629
and a razor in the sink.

570
00:33:28,663 --> 00:33:30,264
Is Trudy finished with you?

571
00:33:30,299 --> 00:33:31,799
This is our pied-à-terre.

572
00:33:31,833 --> 00:33:33,734
Does your father
bring prostitutes here

573
00:33:33,768 --> 00:33:35,202
or is it just for yours?

574
00:33:35,237 --> 00:33:36,770
I want to be taken home.

575
00:33:36,805 --> 00:33:39,340
Your apartment's
been overrun with vermin.

576
00:33:39,374 --> 00:33:40,975
They're spraying all day.

577
00:33:41,009 --> 00:33:43,144
Oh.

578
00:33:43,178 --> 00:33:46,112
I didn't remember that.
I want to get my things.

579
00:33:46,147 --> 00:33:49,782
It's raining very hard out
and it's, well--

580
00:33:49,817 --> 00:33:51,717
it's St. Patrick's Day.

581
00:33:51,752 --> 00:33:54,354
- It's May.
- No, it's not.

582
00:33:55,889 --> 00:33:57,690
And who knows what's out there?

583
00:34:00,393 --> 00:34:03,728
I'll have the cook make
your favorite for dinner.

584
00:34:23,955 --> 00:34:27,557
- Morning.
- You look fresh.

585
00:34:27,591 --> 00:34:29,726
Where's my secretary?

586
00:34:29,761 --> 00:34:31,593
Or is this how
they do it at CGC,

587
00:34:31,628 --> 00:34:33,495
just let yourself in?

588
00:34:33,530 --> 00:34:34,964
I didn't want to wait out there

589
00:34:34,998 --> 00:34:37,967
because this whole visit
is confidential.

590
00:34:38,001 --> 00:34:39,802
You want to quit already?

591
00:34:42,205 --> 00:34:44,073
When you told me
about the merger,

592
00:34:44,107 --> 00:34:46,308
I hoped he would
rub off on you,

593
00:34:46,342 --> 00:34:48,409
not the other way around.

594
00:34:48,443 --> 00:34:50,912
He's getting
everything he wants

595
00:34:50,946 --> 00:34:53,381
and obviously
you're on his side.

596
00:34:53,415 --> 00:34:55,684
Why did you do it at all
if there are sides?

597
00:34:55,718 --> 00:34:57,318
You could have just tried
to hire me back.

598
00:34:57,352 --> 00:34:58,853
You never even
asked me to lunch.

599
00:34:58,888 --> 00:35:02,923
Yes, Peggy, we risked
our entire company

600
00:35:02,957 --> 00:35:05,258
just so I could have you in
this office complaining again.

601
00:35:05,293 --> 00:35:07,494
Well, he can't drink like you.

602
00:35:07,528 --> 00:35:08,996
And you must know that
because nobody can.

603
00:35:09,030 --> 00:35:11,464
- Peggy, he's a grown man.
- So are you.

604
00:35:12,567 --> 00:35:14,001
Move forward.

605
00:35:20,240 --> 00:35:22,541
You're going to be fine.
With Burt Peterson gone,

606
00:35:22,576 --> 00:35:24,476
Kenny in Detroit, everything's
going to fall in your in-box.

607
00:35:24,511 --> 00:35:26,045
What about Cutler?

608
00:35:26,080 --> 00:35:27,513
What about every time
there's a change around here,

609
00:35:27,547 --> 00:35:29,182
I get knocked down
to a worse office?

610
00:35:29,216 --> 00:35:31,184
Come in, Scarlett.

611
00:35:31,218 --> 00:35:33,786
Mr. Campbell,
I'm sorry to interrupt,

612
00:35:33,821 --> 00:35:35,220
but you're needed on the phone.

613
00:35:35,254 --> 00:35:36,822
What now, Clara?

614
00:35:38,490 --> 00:35:40,525
Is she injured?

615
00:35:40,559 --> 00:35:42,327
No, but there's been a fire.

616
00:35:42,361 --> 00:35:44,830
Call Henry at Mohawk.
See if he can meet tomorrow.

617
00:35:44,864 --> 00:35:47,165
I have no idea how long
this will take.

618
00:35:47,200 --> 00:35:50,135
Trudy?

619
00:35:58,076 --> 00:36:00,510
I don't know what it is.

620
00:36:00,545 --> 00:36:03,447
I just don't want
to think about anything.

621
00:36:03,481 --> 00:36:05,716
Who told you
you were allowed to think?

622
00:36:11,422 --> 00:36:15,792
So, what do I do now?

623
00:36:18,363 --> 00:36:21,265
You fall asleep
the minute I close that door.

624
00:36:22,667 --> 00:36:24,533
I'm flying upstate,

625
00:36:24,568 --> 00:36:28,237
and when I come back,
I want you ready for me.

626
00:36:30,507 --> 00:36:33,208
I can do that
standing on my head.

627
00:36:41,817 --> 00:36:43,652
And I'm taking this.

628
00:36:44,787 --> 00:36:47,722
Really?
Come on.

629
00:36:47,757 --> 00:36:49,491
I'm taking it.

630
00:36:54,029 --> 00:36:56,530
Something's come up.
Do you have a minute for Clara?

631
00:36:57,565 --> 00:36:59,566
Pete Campbell's secretary.

632
00:36:59,601 --> 00:37:01,502
Certainly.

633
00:37:03,805 --> 00:37:06,774
Mr. Campbell had an emergency
and Mr. Draper is out,

634
00:37:06,808 --> 00:37:08,909
so I wanted to make sure you
knew that we were rescheduling

635
00:37:08,943 --> 00:37:10,444
this afternoon's
meeting with Mohawk.

636
00:37:10,478 --> 00:37:12,011
Absolutely not.

637
00:37:12,045 --> 00:37:13,513
What the hell
is going on around here?

638
00:37:13,547 --> 00:37:15,315
Ready to go?

639
00:37:15,349 --> 00:37:17,983
I am, but apparently Pete
Campbell wants to move it.

640
00:37:18,018 --> 00:37:20,419
We can't cancel
the meeting to show a client

641
00:37:20,453 --> 00:37:22,354
how important he is.
When can he go?

642
00:37:22,388 --> 00:37:23,989
It doesn't matter. We should
go up there right away.

643
00:37:24,024 --> 00:37:26,591
It's raining pretty hard.
We can wait a couple hours.

644
00:37:26,626 --> 00:37:30,462
Don't worry about that. Once we're above
the clouds, it's sunny as summer.

645
00:37:38,370 --> 00:37:40,104
How long have you
been doing this?

646
00:37:40,139 --> 00:37:41,840
Not now.

647
00:37:52,483 --> 00:37:54,351
There we go.

648
00:37:54,385 --> 00:37:56,753
You can relax now.
We're leveled off.

649
00:37:58,389 --> 00:38:00,523
I am relaxed.

650
00:38:06,463 --> 00:38:08,464
Sometimes when you're flying,

651
00:38:08,498 --> 00:38:11,033
you think you're right side up,
but you're really upside down.

652
00:38:12,369 --> 00:38:14,337
Really?

653
00:38:14,371 --> 00:38:16,339
Got to watch your instruments.

654
00:38:25,281 --> 00:38:28,850
You don't want to take in
the wonder of God's majesty?

655
00:38:28,885 --> 00:38:32,053
I like to read on planes.
I don't like to talk.

656
00:38:32,088 --> 00:38:33,821
But you're gonna talk
to Henry Lammott.

657
00:38:33,856 --> 00:38:35,857
I mean, you're the one
that knows him.

658
00:38:35,892 --> 00:38:38,292
Does it matter?

659
00:38:38,326 --> 00:38:40,127
No matter what I say,

660
00:38:40,161 --> 00:38:42,863
you're the guy who flew us
up here in his own plane.

661
00:38:44,599 --> 00:38:46,833
I guess that's true.

662
00:38:53,441 --> 00:38:55,441
I don't know if Joanie's awake.

663
00:38:55,475 --> 00:38:57,110
I really don't need to see her.

664
00:38:57,144 --> 00:38:59,078
You can just give
Kevin my gift.

665
00:39:01,748 --> 00:39:03,950
Oh. Oh.

666
00:39:05,085 --> 00:39:07,353
Hello.

667
00:39:07,388 --> 00:39:09,422
I really wasn't planning
on dropping in.

668
00:39:11,190 --> 00:39:13,926
I just wanted to see
if you were feeling better.

669
00:39:13,960 --> 00:39:17,262
The hospital wouldn't tell me anything
because I'm not immediate family.

670
00:39:17,297 --> 00:39:19,097
He's two years old.
He'll play with the bow.

671
00:39:19,132 --> 00:39:21,366
Sit down. Have a snack.

672
00:39:21,401 --> 00:39:24,269
No, that's all. Don't want to be
away from the office too long.

673
00:39:24,304 --> 00:39:26,437
Although I left
my overcoat on my chair,

674
00:39:26,471 --> 00:39:28,906
so they know I'm there.

675
00:39:28,941 --> 00:39:32,944
Well, it's nice meeting you.

676
00:39:39,217 --> 00:39:41,085
He's adorable.

677
00:39:41,119 --> 00:39:43,186
He's too young.

678
00:39:43,220 --> 00:39:45,055
I can tell you from experience

679
00:39:45,089 --> 00:39:47,857
that younger men are not
intimidated by powerful women.

680
00:39:47,891 --> 00:39:51,194
- He's not interested.
- He saved your life.

681
00:39:51,228 --> 00:39:53,529
It was just a cyst on my ovary.

682
00:39:53,564 --> 00:39:56,899
I would have been fine.
He's worrying about his job.

683
00:39:56,934 --> 00:39:59,301
Well, why wouldn't he?

684
00:39:59,336 --> 00:40:01,403
It doesn't take away
what he did.

685
00:40:01,438 --> 00:40:03,638
Honestly, Joan, every good deed

686
00:40:03,673 --> 00:40:05,607
is not part of a plan.

687
00:40:10,513 --> 00:40:13,315
She left the teakettle on.
It was mostly smoke.

688
00:40:13,350 --> 00:40:15,416
Can you get Henry Lammott
on the phone?

689
00:40:18,520 --> 00:40:21,322
I will, but Mr. Lammott
already called for you.

690
00:40:21,357 --> 00:40:23,924
Don and Ted thought
it was best not to wait.

691
00:40:23,959 --> 00:40:26,760
Really?
They went without me?

692
00:40:26,795 --> 00:40:29,930
Yes. Apparently it
went very well.

693
00:40:29,965 --> 00:40:32,565
Damn it, Clara.
They went without me.

694
00:40:32,600 --> 00:40:34,968
Therefore, it did not
go very well.

695
00:40:35,003 --> 00:40:38,638
You do understand that your
employment here is tied to me?

696
00:40:38,672 --> 00:40:40,307
And if things
happen without me,

697
00:40:40,341 --> 00:40:42,342
they'll eventually
happen without you.

698
00:40:45,546 --> 00:40:47,480
Don't feel bad that you were
taking care of your mother.

699
00:40:47,514 --> 00:40:49,515
My mother can go to hell.

700
00:40:49,549 --> 00:40:51,517
Ted Chaough can fly her there.

701
00:40:51,551 --> 00:40:54,286
Do you want me to get
Mr. Lammott on the phone?

702
00:40:54,321 --> 00:40:57,456
Can you give me a minute?

703
00:41:10,100 --> 00:41:12,101
I'm here.

704
00:41:16,071 --> 00:41:18,239
Where are you going?

705
00:41:19,441 --> 00:41:21,308
I think it's time to go home.

706
00:41:21,343 --> 00:41:22,744
Not yet.

707
00:41:22,778 --> 00:41:25,346
I think this is over.

708
00:41:25,380 --> 00:41:29,050
It's over when I say it's over.

709
00:41:33,354 --> 00:41:37,124
I had a dream that you
crashed in that plane.

710
00:41:39,060 --> 00:41:41,494
But I'm back.

711
00:41:41,529 --> 00:41:43,063
I dreamt I went to your funeral

712
00:41:43,097 --> 00:41:44,765
and Megan cried on my shoulder.

713
00:41:44,799 --> 00:41:48,901
- Stop it.
- And then I went back to Arnold

714
00:41:48,935 --> 00:41:52,171
and I made love to him
and I said,

715
00:41:52,205 --> 00:41:55,941
"I've been away,
but I'm home."

716
00:41:55,976 --> 00:41:58,744
It means you missed me.

717
00:42:00,781 --> 00:42:02,581
No.

718
00:42:05,918 --> 00:42:09,420
It means it's time
to really go home.

719
00:42:11,824 --> 00:42:14,059
This is over,

720
00:42:14,093 --> 00:42:16,094
and not just this.

721
00:42:27,338 --> 00:42:30,107
It's easy to give up something
when you're satisfied.

722
00:42:31,910 --> 00:42:33,744
It's easy to give up something

723
00:42:33,778 --> 00:42:35,579
when you're ashamed.

724
00:42:42,219 --> 00:42:44,286
Please.

725
00:42:56,632 --> 00:42:58,433
Let's go.

726
00:43:32,399 --> 00:43:34,868
Burt Peterson's gone.
That leaves me,

727
00:43:34,902 --> 00:43:37,036
Jim Torkelson,
and Lawrence Harris.

728
00:43:37,071 --> 00:43:40,172
You've got Roger, Pete,
Ken, and Bob Benson.

729
00:43:40,206 --> 00:43:42,507
But you've got your creatives
Peggy, Cecil, and Beanie.

730
00:43:42,541 --> 00:43:44,476
We lost Margie, Koch,
and Steve Hagan.

731
00:43:44,510 --> 00:43:46,812
I don't know who Peggy
counts for, but we need Bob.

732
00:43:46,846 --> 00:43:50,248
Bob's got to go.
Last hired, first fired.

733
00:43:54,853 --> 00:43:57,889
Very well.

734
00:43:57,923 --> 00:44:00,892
But before I cross him off,
let me remind you

735
00:44:00,926 --> 00:44:03,060
that Bob has been very
involved in Ken's accounts,

736
00:44:03,095 --> 00:44:05,128
and with Ken servicing Detroit,

737
00:44:05,163 --> 00:44:06,629
I don't know how long it'll
take Lawrence to catch up.

738
00:44:06,664 --> 00:44:08,865
Fine, Lawrence is gone.
Are we done here?

739
00:44:11,269 --> 00:44:14,370
The secretarial staff?

740
00:44:50,306 --> 00:44:52,206
And instead of being afraid,

741
00:44:52,240 --> 00:44:55,775
I realized I should just ask
for a couple of weeks off.

742
00:44:55,810 --> 00:44:58,946
They write people out
all the time.

743
00:44:58,980 --> 00:45:01,014
Or I could shoot in advance

744
00:45:01,049 --> 00:45:03,383
and maybe we could go
to Honolulu again.

745
00:45:03,417 --> 00:45:05,819
<i>This time without business.</i>

746
00:45:05,854 --> 00:45:08,787
I just thought it would
be fun to go on a trip,

747
00:45:08,822 --> 00:45:11,423
the two of us for a bit
without the kids.

748
00:45:27,139 --> 00:45:29,140
Peter.

749
00:45:29,175 --> 00:45:31,276
They shot
that poor Kennedy boy.

750
00:45:31,310 --> 00:45:33,144
That was years ago, Mother.

751
00:45:33,179 --> 00:45:35,513
I just saw it
on the television.

752
00:45:36,749 --> 00:45:38,449
It's 6:00 AM.

753
00:45:38,484 --> 00:45:40,684
You'll be late for school.

754
00:45:40,718 --> 00:45:42,452
Please just let me sleep.

755
00:45:42,487 --> 00:45:45,555
I don't understand
what's going on.

756
00:45:45,590 --> 00:45:47,657
They're shooting everybody.

757
00:45:49,594 --> 00:45:51,795
<i>Senator Kennedy then going off</i>

758
00:45:51,829 --> 00:45:54,899
<i>into the kitchen area to retire
to his room for the evening,</i>

759
00:45:54,933 --> 00:45:57,433
<i>or at least</i>
<i>for the next hour or so,</i>

760
00:45:57,467 --> 00:46:00,103
<i>the crowd spreading around
him, shaking hands,</i>

761
00:46:00,137 --> 00:46:02,338
<i>clapping him on the back.</i>

